sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM components 
WHERE name = 'Resistor';

external_knowledge:
- 'Members of the electronic family' refers to the components in the components table;
- 'Hidden ability to resist the flow of current' metaphorically refers to components that are resistors, indicated by the keyword 'resistor' in the description;
- Listing in alphabetical order means ordering the names in ascending alphabetical order.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_components, AVG(parameters.min_value) AS avg_min_value
FROM components
JOIN parameters ON components.component_id = parameters.component_id;

SELECT name, description
FROM components
WHERE component_id = 1;
